    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "The father may exert an influence over his children which shall be stronger than the allurements of the world. He should study the disposition and character of the members of his little circle, that he may understand their needs and their dangers and thus be prepared to repress the wrong and encourage the right.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">5<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"RH 8-30-1881\" data-link=\"821.3914\">The Review and Herald, August 30, 1881</span>.</span></a></sup>",
