    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "<strong>Become Acquainted With Varied Dispositions</strong>&mdash;The father should not become so absorbed in business life or in the study of books that he cannot take time to study the natures and necessities of his children. He should help in devising ways by which they may be kept busy in useful labor agreeable to their varying dispositions.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">7<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"CT 127.1\" data-link=\"23.591\">Counsels to Teachers, Parents, and Students, 127, 128</span>.</span></a></sup>",
    "puborder": 663,
